---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { autoUrl, forgeUrl, marketUrl } from '../data/products';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Pricing"
  description="Pricing for the AgentKitProject ecosystem: free to start, optional kit monetization on Market, and pay-as-you-go or bring-your-own-key automation in AgentKitAuto."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h1>Free to start. Monetize when you choose.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Building, publishing, and using Agent Kits across the ecosystem is free to get started, and
        creators can optionally monetize their work. Local-first kit work with the
        <code>agentkitforge</code> CLI and core — create, validate, package, export, and import
        local kits — is always free and needs no account. <strong>AgentKitForge itself is free</strong> —
        building, importing, packaging, exporting, and publishing kits cost nothing; the only usage
        cost is running or chatting with a kit on managed AI, billed at the underlying Anthropic
        model price with <strong>no markup</strong> (or bring your own key and pay Anthropic directly).
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href={marketUrl}>Open AgentKitMarket</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={forgeUrl}>Get AgentKitForge</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Kits on Market</p>
      <h2>List each kit the way that fits.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Kit owners choose how to list each kit on AgentKitMarket — free to download, or
        <strong>premium</strong>, priced per run.
      </p>
      <div class="grid two" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Free</h3>
          <p>List a kit at no cost. Anyone can download it.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Premium</h3>
          <p>
            Set a price per run. A premium kit runs on AgentKitAuto — its files are never handed
            over — and each run charges the buyer your per-run price from their prepaid balance.
            You earn it every time the kit is used, not just once.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="content-panel">
        <h2>Sellers keep 94%.</h2>
        <p>
          The platform fee is 6% — sellers keep 94% of every run of their premium kits. Earnings
          accrue per run and are paid out through Stripe using Stripe Connect.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">AgentKitAuto</p>
      <h2>Two ways to pay for runs.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Automating Agent Kit runs with AgentKitAuto can be paid for with managed credits or by
        bringing your own Anthropic API key.
      </p>
      <div class="grid two" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Managed credits</h3>
          <p>
            Pay only for compute: $0.01 per run plus $0.01 per active minute. Your first 60 active
            minutes are free. Model tokens are billed at cost — no markup. No commitment.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Bring your own Anthropic key</h3>
          <p>
            Connect your own Anthropic API key and pay Anthropic directly for tokens. The same
            compute fee — $0.01 per run plus $0.01 per active minute — still applies; your key is
            encrypted at rest.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-panel">
        <h2>Ready to publish or automate?</h2>
        <p>
          Start free, then monetize on Market or run kits with AgentKitAuto whenever you are ready.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="button" href={marketUrl}>Explore AgentKitMarket</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href={autoUrl}>See AgentKitAuto</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .section:first-child {
    background:
      linear-gradient(135deg, color-mix(in srgb, var(--theme-accent) 13%, transparent), transparent 34rem),
      transparent;
  }
</style>
